Calling all nail enthusiasts i wish i knew this sooner 🙌 
The key to being successful is down to you & what you put into something but here is 3 top tips to help you into your journey within the nail industry. 

1. Invest in good quality training, i wish i had known this before i started my career. At the time I purchased the cheapest course i could to gain a qualification to come away not knowing exactly what to do & therefore spent more money investing into other training to give me the confidence to start within the industry & this took me 2 full years to follow on from that first course i ever took to taking on clients. That’s why i have created courses that give you the confidence, tools & knowledge to work within the industry from leaving your course! Link in bio.

2. Don’t compare yourself to others, we are all on our own journey and you will be where you are meant to be at your own pace. Put in the work & and enjoy what you do & watch as new doors open for you that you never knew existed. 

3. Invest in good quality tools, ditch buying anything just to get started! we have all heard the saying you are only as good as your tools? Or buy cheap buy twice? Well that’s kind of true. If you want a good job done then investing in good quality products such as nail tools and gel brands that are safe and industry approved will make your job easier and your work last longer which keeps your clients happy & coming back. 

If you want to learn more tips and tricks make sure to hit the save and follow button. 
Or for more information on courses visit @gtnacademy or hit the link in bio for course prices & to book.

Did you know?

1 key factor to a long lasting manicures is keeping your nails hydrated with regular use of cuticle oil. 
Our nails shrink in certain temperatures or conditions due to lack of moisture, meaning your gel mani is more likely to chip off as the nail has curled away from the product. Adding oil onto your nails daily will help maintain that gel manicure you just paid for, keeping them fresher looking & last a little longer. ❤️#nailsnailsnails #nailvideosdaily #nailreels #nailsofinstagram #shortnailsdontcare #nailstoinspire #frenchmanicure #nailoil

Back from my break away, refreshed & ready to get back to work ✨🇬🇷

We all make mistakes and no one is perfect always remember that when starting your career in the nail industry! With focus and drive of what you want to achieve you will get there. Don’t be disheartened looking at other peoples work because even with over 6 year’s experience as well as being an educator i still go out the lines! 
The proof if in the pudding with this video 🤦🏽‍♀️ 
Not everything on instagram is picture perfect. 

Here is some tips on how you can perfect your nails and your confidence. 

1.Becoming E-File trained will be a life saver, if you’re struggling with perfecting cuticles or struggling with your infills or even a little bit of builder moved and cures outwith the lines you can fix all this with an E-File. 
(Join my E-File course and i will show you how)

2. Education is key 🔑 invest in good courses and spend time looking into them before you purchase. There is also a lot of free content that is shared online thats you can pick up techniques from. 

3. Practice! It’s a simple one but honestly i would spend hours daily practicing on myself, taking pictures or trying out different techniques even before i had clients, there is no excuse on this one we all have hands to practice on. 

4. Invest in good products and tools! Trust me on this ☝️ on all GTN Academy courses we cover kit building in detail and only use the best tools and products on our courses to ensure you have the best experience and knowledge going forward after your course. 

Link in bio for all GTN Academy courses ✨
